  </folder>
  <purpose>Example Adult Social Care architecture modelled using LGAM layers and ArchiMate.

This file demonstrates how a council might document its ASC technology estate using:
- LGAM layers as the organising structure (folders)
- ArchiMate element types for formal modelling
- ArchiMate relationships between specific systems

The elements represent a typical (illustrative) council's ASC technology stack:
- Liquidlogic for case management
- GOV.UK services (Forms, Pay, One Login)
- Microsoft stack (Azure, Entra ID, Defender)
- NHS Spine and DWP integration
- Power BI for statutory reporting

To use: Open in Archi, review the elements and relationships, then adapt to your council's specific systems.

More information: https://architecture.cddo.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/gds-local/</purpose>
</archimate:model>
